{"id": "duc04-testb-35:5#16", "contents": "Speakers at the service included former Prime Minister Viktor Chernomyrdin and Yuri Yarov, President Boris Yeltsin's first deputy chief of staff. Yarov represented the president at the service, as Yeltsin was recovering from pneumonia in a Moscow hospital. Yarov stated that the shooting in St. Petersburg was a grim lesson for the whole of Russia and that society should know the truth about the crime. The government announced that Starovoitova would be interred in the Alexander Nevsky Monastery in the city's center, alongside some of Russia's greatest national heroes."}
